{
  "local_port": 59628,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What's the best way to calculate percentage off of something?",
  "response": "To calculate the percentage off of something, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Determine the original price**: This is the initial price of the item before any discount is applied.\n\n2. **Determine the discount percentage**: This is the percentage that will be taken off the original price.\n\n3. **Calculate the amount of the discount**: To find the discount amount, multiply the original price by the discount percentage (expressed as a decimal). For example, if the discount is 20%, you would multiply by 0.20.\n\n   \\[\n   \\text{Discount Amount} = \\text{Original Price} \\times \\text{Discount Percentage}\n   \\]\n\n4. **Subtract the discount amount from the original price**: This will give you the final price after the discount is applied.\n\n   \\[\n   \\text{Final Price} = \\text{Original Price} - \\text{Discount Amount}\n   \\]\n\nHere\u2019s an example to illustrate:\n\n- **Original Price**: $100\n- **Discount Percentage**: 20%\n\nStep 3: Calculate the discount amount.\n\n\\[\n\\text{Discount Amount} = 100 \\times 0.20 = 20\n\\]\n\nStep 4: Subtract the discount amount from the original price.\n\n\\[\n\\text{Final Price} = 100 - 20 = 80\n\\]\n\nSo, a 20% discount on an item originally priced at $100 results in a final price of $80.\n\nIf you want to verify the percentage off, you can also calculate the percentage discount from the final price:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Percentage Off} = \\left( \\frac{\\text{Original Price} - \\text{Final Price}}{\\text{Original Price}} \\right) \\times 100\n\\]\n\nUsing the example above:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Percentage Off} = \\left( \\frac{100 - 80}{100} \\right) \\times 100 = 20\\%\n\\]\n\nThis confirms that the final price reflects a 20% discount off the original price.",
